message: Why were these removed in the first place? It's a diverse album. Leave it alone!
there's no reggae here, only reggae fusion

After reslistening to the album, I've determined this one to be predominately alternative hip hop and alternative rock, with a lot of dub mixed in. There are also influences from electronic music, and a few remnants left of reggae. There's elements of both indie hip hop and indie rock, as well as experimental hip hop and experimental rock. Very hard to classify this album with only a few genres...

Listened through the whole album, and adjusted the genres to better fit the album; it's mostly Reggae fusion, but elements of pop, hip hop, and electronic are seen as well; the song Obstacles and Reservoir are straight up Post-rock... very diverse album!
